    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <persName role="author">Nathan Benjamin</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><persName>Leeser</persName> Papers</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Decr. 11th 1864</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">The attention of a<lb/> number of influential members of the various
                congregations<lb/> was called to the proceedings of a meeting held<lb/> in your city
                last month, for the purpose of amending<lb/> the constitution of the
                    <placeName>United States</placeName> so as to disfranchise<lb/> the Jewish
                Community. After a full interchange<lb/> of views as to the probability of congress
                recommending<lb/> the amendment, it was unanimously adopted,<lb/> that the most
                powerful argument that we could<lb/> use to defeat the plan of the meeting was
                for<lb/> the Jews to be <hi rend="underline">Silent</hi>, yet <hi rend="underline"
                    >watchful</hi>, &amp; it is<lb/> my dear Sir the object of this letter to ask
                of<lb/> you, if you coincide in this view, that at<lb/> the present time you will
                refrain from publishing<lb/> or writing any article on the subject in<lb/> your
                Occident, as by agitation it might give<lb/> an importance to the subject which as
                yet<lb/> it has not assumed.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Trusting you are in the enjoyment of health</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I am my dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Yours very Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Benj Nathan</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
